Fixes a bug Routes, which is was causing some api methods to be ignored completely

See the following method

```php
class Test {
    /**
     * @param string $p1 {@from query}
     * @param string $p2
     */
    function bug($p1, $p2) {

    }
}
```
Before this fix `/test/bug/{p2}` api is not created at all

After this fix it can be accessed similar to the following example

    /test/bug/2?p1=1

Fixed the EventDispatcher, listening to Restler events is now possible in the following ways

```php
<?php //index.php

//adding event listeners with the class
Restler::addListener('onCall',function(){
    echo "Restler::addListener('onCall')\n";
});

$r = new Restler();

//adding event listeners with the instance
$r->addListener('onGet',function(){
    echo "\$r->addListener('onGet')\n";
});

//calling the event method
$r->onNegotiate(function(){
    echo "\$r->onNegotiate()\n";
});

//bulk listening
$r->on(array(
    'call' =>function(){
        echo "on call\n";
    },
    'get' =>function(){
        echo "on get\n";
    },
));
$r->addAPIClass('Say');
$r->handle();
```

above code on the hello world example gives

    $r->addListener('onGet')
    on get
    $r->onNegotiate()
    Restler::addListener('onCall')
    on call
    "Hello world!"

Fixes #186

Improving Routes, when an api method has only one parameter mapped to request body, allow it to be parsed directly from the request body

For example if our api method is

```php
    /**
     * Custom Class Parameter
     *
     * @param int    $id
     * @param Author $author
     *
     * @return Author
     */
    function putAuthor($id, Author $author)
    {
        return $author;
    }
```

before this commit only way to pass the data is with this body

```json
{
    "author":  {
        "name": "Arul",
        "email": "arul@luracast.com"
    }
}
```

This commit allows to accept the following request too along with the above

```json
{
  "name": "Arul",
  "email": "arul@luracast.com"
}
```

Discussed today on #185

Set the default value of Object::$separatorChar to null to avoid breaking keys with dot to sub object. Fixes #179

If such breaking up is desired It should be configured in the index.php as shown below

```php
use Luracast\Restler\Data\Object;

Object::$separatorChar = '.';
```

